description:
Right now we throw an exception if Dynamic type has values that are not comparable with the second argument value:
```sql
CREATE TABLE test (d Dynamic) ENGINE=Memory;
INSERT INTO test VALUES (42::Int64), ([1, 2, 3]);
SELECT * FROM test WHERE d = 42;
Received exception from server (version 25.8.4):
Code: 43. DB::Exception: Received from localhost:9000. DB::Exception: Illegal types of arguments (Array(Int64), UInt8) of function equals: while executing 'FUNCTION equals(d :: 0, 42_UInt8 :: 1) -> equals(__table1.d, 42_UInt8) Nullable(UInt8) : 3'. (ILLEGAL_TYPE_OF_ARGUMENT)
(query: SELECT * FROM test WHERE d = 42;)
```
It happens because by default we execute function on all types inside Dynamic separately and then combine the result. But for `equals` function we can just return 0 for rows with not comparable types.
